    Happiness Dataset

    happiness.Rd

    A data frame containing a happiness survey and demographic data. This data are fictitious.

    happiness

    Format

    A data frame with 460 rows and 11 variables:

    ID

    character. A unique identifier.

    Date

    date. Date of the interview.

    Sex

    factor. Sex coded as Male or Female.

    Race

    factor. Race coded as an 8-level factor.

    Age

    integer. Age in years.

    Education

    factor. Education coded as a 13-level factor.

    Income

    double. Annual income in US dollars.

    IQ

    double. Adult intelligence quotient. This variable has a large amount of missing data.

    Zip

    character. USPS Zip code.

    Children

    integer. Number of children.

    Happy

    factor. Agreement with the statement "I am happy most of the time", coded as Strongly Disagree , Disagree, Neutral, Agree, or Strongly Agree.

    Source

    The data were randomly generated using functions from the wakefield package.
